attributes.body:
A City, and a Place Away

A familiar face...

I met a great guy by the name of Edgar while in Costa Rica. He told me to stop in when I arrived in Colombia, and he really meant it. Immediately he suggested I should stay for New Years (over a month away).

Flying

Edgar has a few buddies that are into Paragliding. I managed to get up in a paraglider for a few minutes with a buddy of his... And am now contemplating taking some lessons.

photos.title: Tamales
photos.description: These are some of the best tamales of my life. They're wrapped up so thickly with plantain leaves that they're solid cups when cut in half. Inside is chicken, there are even some bones, which I suspect, during the long cooking process, adds a lot to the gelatinous texture.

photos.title: Colombian Police Motorcycle
photos.description: For some reason you often see police riding two up. It's sensible for transit, but not for pursuit.

photos.title: Perros Calientes
photos.description: Death machine of a hot dog.

photos.title: Perros Calientes
photos.description: It comes with a hot dog, shredded chicken, carnitas, a thick layer of fried cheese, tiny ham squares, and it's topped off with a boiled cornish hen egg on a toothpick. Incredible.

photos.title: Perros Calientes
photos.description: I think he's actually beginning to have a heart attack in this photo.

photos.title: Candelita
photos.description: What a cutie pie.

photos.title: Coca Tea
photos.description: Tried it, can't say it beats a cup of coffee though.

photos.title: Arepas Chocos
photos.description: Sweet corn, with a cheesy center. Simply incredible.

photos.title: Martini
photos.description: This is Martini, an you can see Chispita in the background.

photos.title: Edgar
photos.description: Making Pizza

photos.title: Edgar
photos.description: It was a good lunch.

photos.title: The Slope
photos.description: Where you take off from.

photos.title: Flying Feet
photos.description: Got to go paragliding for the first time. It was amazingly casual, and really felt like flying.

photos.title: Circus
photos.description: The circus is in town.

photos.title: Christmas Deorations
photos.description: This is at Edgar's mother's house, and reminds me a lot of the sort of decorations my grandmother used to set up.

photos.title: Edgar's House
photos.description: Edgar has 8 dogs! Here he is showing me some of his fruit trees, only some of the dogs following us.

photos.title: Downtown Bucaramanga
photos.description: Here's the city from Edgar's office on the 7th floor.

photos.title: Downtown Bucaramanga
photos.description: A panoramic shot from Edgar's office.

photos.title: 6 Dogs Eating Dinner
photos.description: Feeding 8 dogs can be a little tricky, but if you get the timing just right, things work out.

photos.title: Dog Named Martini
photos.description: Martini is a never-ending well of happiness, as is the person holding him.

photos.title: Foods of Bucaramanga
photos.description: This photo does a good job of summarizing a lot of the food around here. Hot chocolate served with cheese is a staple (they put the cheese in the hot chocolate), as are sweet breads, cheesy breads, and tamales.

photos.title: Water Fountains
photos.description: These public water fountains attracted a crowd of children to jump around in them.
